%N A394286 Decimal expansion of Product_{p prime} (1 - 2/(p^2*(p+1))).
%C A394286 The asymptotic probability that the greatest common divisor of two positive integers selected independently at random equals their greatest common unitary divisor.
%C A394286 In other words, for all primes p, if these two integers are both divisible by p, then they have equal p-adic valuations (exponents of p in their prime factorizations).
%F A394286 Equals zeta(2) * Product_{p prime} (1 - 1/p^2 - 2/p^3 + 2/p^4) = A013661 * A394006.
%F A394286 Equals (1/zeta(2)) * Product_{p prime} (1 + 1/(p+1)^2) = A059956 * A065486.
%e A394286 0.769975239128165285596843943228823906161378619145338...
%o A394286 (PARI) prodeulerrat(1 - 2/(p^2*(p+1)))
%Y A394286 Cf. A013661, A059956, A065486, A077610, A394006, A394287.
